41/*
42 * Default simple round-robin algorithm.
43 * Just interates the streams in the order they appear.
44 */
45
46static void
47sctp_ss_default_add(struct sctp_tcb *, struct sctp_association *,
48 struct sctp_stream_out *,
49 struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *, int);
50
51static void
52sctp_ss_default_remove(struct sctp_tcb *, struct sctp_association *,
53 struct sctp_stream_out *,
54 struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *, int);
55
56static void
57sctp_ss_default_init(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_association *asoc,
58 int holds_lock)
59{
60 uint16_t i;
61
62 if (holds_lock == 0) {
63 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
64 }
65 asoc->ss_data.locked_on_sending = NULL;
66 asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream = NULL;
67 TAILQ_INIT(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel);
68 /*
69 * If there is data in the stream queues already,
70 * the scheduler of an existing association has
71 * been changed. We need to add all stream queues
72 * to the wheel.
73 */
74 for (i = 0; i < stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt; i++) {
75 stcb->asoc.ss_functions.sctp_ss_add_to_stream(stcb, &stcb->asoc,
76 &stcb->asoc.strmout[i],
77 NULL, 1);
78 }
79 if (holds_lock == 0) {
80 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
81 }
82 return;
83}
84
85static void
86sctp_ss_default_clear(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_association *asoc,
87 int clear_values SCTP_UNUSED, int holds_lock)
88{
89 if (holds_lock == 0) {
90 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
91 }
92 while (!TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel)) {
93 struct sctp_stream_out *strq;
94
95 strq = TAILQ_FIRST(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel);
96 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel, strq, ss_params.rr.next_spoke);
97 strq->ss_params.rr.next_spoke.tqe_next = NULL;
98 strq->ss_params.rr.next_spoke.tqe_prev = NULL;
99 }
100 asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream = NULL;
101 if (holds_lock == 0) {
102 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
103 }
104 return;
105}
106
107static void
108sctp_ss_default_init_stream(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_stream_out *strq, struct sctp_stream_out *with_strq)
109{
110 if (with_strq != NULL) {
111 if (stcb->asoc.ss_data.locked_on_sending == with_strq) {
112 stcb->asoc.ss_data.locked_on_sending = strq;
113 }
114 if (stcb->asoc.ss_data.last_out_stream == with_strq) {
115 stcb->asoc.ss_data.last_out_stream = strq;
116 }
117 }
118 strq->ss_params.rr.next_spoke.tqe_next = NULL;
119 strq->ss_params.rr.next_spoke.tqe_prev = NULL;
120 return;
121}
122
123static void
124sctp_ss_default_add(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_association *asoc,
125 struct sctp_stream_out *strq,
126 struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp SCTP_UNUSED, int holds_lock)
127{
128 if (holds_lock == 0) {
129 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
130 }
131 /* Add to wheel if not already on it and stream queue not empty */
132 if (!TAILQ_EMPTY(&strq->outqueue) &&
133 (strq->ss_params.rr.next_spoke.tqe_next == NULL) &&
134 (strq->ss_params.rr.next_spoke.tqe_prev == NULL)) {
135 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel,
136 strq, ss_params.rr.next_spoke);
137 }
138 if (holds_lock == 0) {
139 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
140 }
141 return;
142}

144static int
145sctp_ss_default_is_empty(struct sctp_tcb *stcb SCTP_UNUSED, struct sctp_association *asoc)
146{
147 if (TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel)) {
148 return (1);
149 } else {
150 return (0);
151 }
152}
153
154static void
155sctp_ss_default_remove(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_association *asoc,
156 struct sctp_stream_out *strq,
157 struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp SCTP_UNUSED, int holds_lock)
158{
159 if (holds_lock == 0) {
160 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
161 }
162 /* Remove from wheel if stream queue is empty and actually is on the wheel */
163 if (TAILQ_EMPTY(&strq->outqueue) &&
164 (strq->ss_params.rr.next_spoke.tqe_next != NULL ||
165 strq->ss_params.rr.next_spoke.tqe_prev != NULL)) {
166 if (asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream == strq) {
167 asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream = TAILQ_PREV(asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream,
168 sctpwheel_listhead,
169 ss_params.rr.next_spoke);
170 if (asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream == NULL) {
171 asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream = TAILQ_LAST(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel,
172 sctpwheel_listhead);
173 }
174 if (asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream == strq) {
175 asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream = NULL;
176 }
177 }
178 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel, strq, ss_params.rr.next_spoke);
179 strq->ss_params.rr.next_spoke.tqe_next = NULL;
180 strq->ss_params.rr.next_spoke.tqe_prev = NULL;
181 }
182 if (holds_lock == 0) {
183 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
184 }
185 return;
186}

188static struct sctp_stream_out *
189sctp_ss_default_select(struct sctp_tcb *stcb SCTP_UNUSED, struct sctp_nets *net,
190 struct sctp_association *asoc)
191{
192 struct sctp_stream_out *strq, *strqt;
193
194 if (asoc->ss_data.locked_on_sending) {
195 return (asoc->ss_data.locked_on_sending);
196 }
197 strqt = asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream;
198default_again:
199 /* Find the next stream to use */
200 if (strqt == NULL) {
201 strq = TAILQ_FIRST(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel);
202 } else {
203 strq = TAILQ_NEXT(strqt, ss_params.rr.next_spoke);
204 if (strq == NULL) {
205 strq = TAILQ_FIRST(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel);
206 }
207 }
208
209 /* If CMT is off, we must validate that
210 * the stream in question has the first
211 * item pointed towards are network destination
212 * requested by the caller. Note that if we
213 * turn out to be locked to a stream (assigning
214 * TSN's then we must stop, since we cannot
215 * look for another stream with data to send
216 * to that destination). In CMT's case, by
217 * skipping this check, we will send one
218 * data packet towards the requested net.
219 */
220 if (net != NULL && strq != NULL &&
221 SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_cmt_on_off) == 0) {
222 if (TAILQ_FIRST(&strq->outqueue) &&
223 TAILQ_FIRST(&strq->outqueue)->net != NULL &&
224 TAILQ_FIRST(&strq->outqueue)->net != net) {
225 if (strq == asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream) {
226 return (NULL);
227 } else {
228 strqt = strq;
229 goto default_again;
230 }
231 }
232 }
233 return (strq);
234}

236static void
237sctp_ss_default_scheduled(struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
238 struct sctp_nets *net SCTP_UNUSED,
239 struct sctp_association *asoc,
240 struct sctp_stream_out *strq,
241 int moved_how_much SCTP_UNUSED)
242{
243 struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp;
244
245 asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream = strq;
246 if (stcb->asoc.idata_supported == 0) {
247 sp = TAILQ_FIRST(&strq->outqueue);
248 if ((sp != NULL) && (sp->some_taken == 1)) {
249 stcb->asoc.ss_data.locked_on_sending = strq;
250 } else {
251 stcb->asoc.ss_data.locked_on_sending = NULL;
252 }
253 } else {
254 stcb->asoc.ss_data.locked_on_sending = NULL;
255 }
256 return;
257}

263 /* Nothing to be done here */

283static int
284sctp_ss_default_is_user_msgs_incomplete(struct sctp_tcb *stcb SCTP_UNUSED, struct sctp_association *asoc)
285{
286 struct sctp_stream_out *strq;
287 struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp;
288
289 if (asoc->stream_queue_cnt != 1) {
290 return (0);
291 }
292 strq = asoc->ss_data.locked_on_sending;
293 if (strq == NULL) {
294 return (0);
295 }
296 sp = TAILQ_FIRST(&strq->outqueue);
297 if (sp == NULL) {
298 return (0);
299 }
300 return (!sp->msg_is_complete);
301}
302
303/*
304 * Real round-robin algorithm.
305 * Always interates the streams in ascending order.
306 */
307static void
308sctp_ss_rr_add(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_association *asoc,
309 struct sctp_stream_out *strq,
310 struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp SCTP_UNUSED, int holds_lock)
311{
312 struct sctp_stream_out *strqt;
313
314 if (holds_lock == 0) {
315 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
316 }
317 if (!TAILQ_EMPTY(&strq->outqueue) &&
318 (strq->ss_params.rr.next_spoke.tqe_next == NULL) &&
319 (strq->ss_params.rr.next_spoke.tqe_prev == NULL)) {
320 if (TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel)) {
321 TAILQ_INSERT_HEAD(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel, strq, ss_params.rr.next_spoke);
322 } else {
323 strqt = TAILQ_FIRST(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel);
324 while (strqt != NULL && (strqt->sid < strq->sid)) {
325 strqt = TAILQ_NEXT(strqt, ss_params.rr.next_spoke);
326 }
327 if (strqt != NULL) {
328 TAILQ_INSERT_BEFORE(strqt, strq, ss_params.rr.next_spoke);
329 } else {
330 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel, strq, ss_params.rr.next_spoke);
331 }
332 }
333 }
334 if (holds_lock == 0) {
335 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
336 }
337 return;
338}
339
340/*
341 * Real round-robin per packet algorithm.
342 * Always interates the streams in ascending order and
343 * only fills messages of the same stream in a packet.
344 */
345static struct sctp_stream_out *
346sctp_ss_rrp_select(struct sctp_tcb *stcb SCTP_UNUSED, struct sctp_nets *net SCTP_UNUSED,
347 struct sctp_association *asoc)
348{
349 return (asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream);
350}
351
352static void
353sctp_ss_rrp_packet_done(struct sctp_tcb *stcb SCTP_UNUSED, struct sctp_nets *net,
354 struct sctp_association *asoc)
355{
356 struct sctp_stream_out *strq, *strqt;
357
358 strqt = asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream;
359rrp_again:
360 /* Find the next stream to use */
361 if (strqt == NULL) {
362 strq = TAILQ_FIRST(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel);
363 } else {
364 strq = TAILQ_NEXT(strqt, ss_params.rr.next_spoke);
365 if (strq == NULL) {
366 strq = TAILQ_FIRST(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel);
367 }
368 }
369
370 /* If CMT is off, we must validate that
371 * the stream in question has the first
372 * item pointed towards are network destination
373 * requested by the caller. Note that if we
374 * turn out to be locked to a stream (assigning
375 * TSN's then we must stop, since we cannot
376 * look for another stream with data to send
377 * to that destination). In CMT's case, by
378 * skipping this check, we will send one
379 * data packet towards the requested net.
380 */
381 if (net != NULL && strq != NULL &&
382 SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_cmt_on_off) == 0) {
383 if (TAILQ_FIRST(&strq->outqueue) &&
384 TAILQ_FIRST(&strq->outqueue)->net != NULL &&
385 TAILQ_FIRST(&strq->outqueue)->net != net) {
386 if (strq == asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream) {
387 strq = NULL;
388 } else {
389 strqt = strq;
390 goto rrp_again;
391 }
392 }
393 }
394 asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream = strq;
395 return;
396}

398/*
399 * Priority algorithm.
400 * Always prefers streams based on their priority id.
401 */
402static void
403sctp_ss_prio_clear(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_association *asoc,
404 int clear_values, int holds_lock)
405{
406 if (holds_lock == 0) {
407 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
408 }
409 while (!TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel)) {
410 struct sctp_stream_out *strq;
411
412 strq = TAILQ_FIRST(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel);
413 if (clear_values) {
414 strq->ss_params.prio.priority = 0;
415 }
416 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel, strq, ss_params.prio.next_spoke);
417 strq->ss_params.prio.next_spoke.tqe_next = NULL;
418 strq->ss_params.prio.next_spoke.tqe_prev = NULL;
419 }
420 asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream = NULL;
421 if (holds_lock == 0) {
422 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
423 }
424 return;
425}

427static void
428sctp_ss_prio_init_stream(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_stream_out *strq, struct sctp_stream_out *with_strq)
429{
430 if (with_strq != NULL) {
431 if (stcb->asoc.ss_data.locked_on_sending == with_strq) {
432 stcb->asoc.ss_data.locked_on_sending = strq;
433 }
434 if (stcb->asoc.ss_data.last_out_stream == with_strq) {
435 stcb->asoc.ss_data.last_out_stream = strq;
436 }
437 }
438 strq->ss_params.prio.next_spoke.tqe_next = NULL;
439 strq->ss_params.prio.next_spoke.tqe_prev = NULL;
440 if (with_strq != NULL) {
441 strq->ss_params.prio.priority = with_strq->ss_params.prio.priority;
442 } else {
443 strq->ss_params.prio.priority = 0;
444 }
445 return;
446}
447
448static void
449sctp_ss_prio_add(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_association *asoc,
450 struct sctp_stream_out *strq, struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp SCTP_UNUSED,
451 int holds_lock)
452{
453 struct sctp_stream_out *strqt;
454
455 if (holds_lock == 0) {
456 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
457 }
458 /* Add to wheel if not already on it and stream queue not empty */
459 if (!TAILQ_EMPTY(&strq->outqueue) &&
460 (strq->ss_params.prio.next_spoke.tqe_next == NULL) &&
461 (strq->ss_params.prio.next_spoke.tqe_prev == NULL)) {
462 if (TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel)) {
463 TAILQ_INSERT_HEAD(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel, strq, ss_params.prio.next_spoke);
464 } else {
465 strqt = TAILQ_FIRST(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel);
466 while (strqt != NULL && strqt->ss_params.prio.priority < strq->ss_params.prio.priority) {
467 strqt = TAILQ_NEXT(strqt, ss_params.prio.next_spoke);
468 }
469 if (strqt != NULL) {
470 TAILQ_INSERT_BEFORE(strqt, strq, ss_params.prio.next_spoke);
471 } else {
472 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel, strq, ss_params.prio.next_spoke);
473 }
474 }
475 }
476 if (holds_lock == 0) {
477 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
478 }
479 return;
480}

482static void
483sctp_ss_prio_remove(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_association *asoc,
484 struct sctp_stream_out *strq, struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp SCTP_UNUSED,
485 int holds_lock)
486{
487 if (holds_lock == 0) {
488 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
489 }
490 /* Remove from wheel if stream queue is empty and actually is on the wheel */
491 if (TAILQ_EMPTY(&strq->outqueue) &&
492 (strq->ss_params.prio.next_spoke.tqe_next != NULL ||
493 strq->ss_params.prio.next_spoke.tqe_prev != NULL)) {
494 if (asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream == strq) {
495 asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream = TAILQ_PREV(asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream, sctpwheel_listhead,
496 ss_params.prio.next_spoke);
497 if (asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream == NULL) {
498 asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream = TAILQ_LAST(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel,
499 sctpwheel_listhead);
500 }
501 if (asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream == strq) {
502 asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream = NULL;
503 }
504 }
505 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel, strq, ss_params.prio.next_spoke);
506 strq->ss_params.prio.next_spoke.tqe_next = NULL;
507 strq->ss_params.prio.next_spoke.tqe_prev = NULL;
508 }
509 if (holds_lock == 0) {
510 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
511 }
512 return;
513}

515static struct sctp_stream_out*
516sctp_ss_prio_select(struct sctp_tcb *stcb SCTP_UNUSED, struct sctp_nets *net,
517 struct sctp_association *asoc)
518{
519 struct sctp_stream_out *strq, *strqt, *strqn;
520
521 if (asoc->ss_data.locked_on_sending) {
522 return (asoc->ss_data.locked_on_sending);
523 }
524 strqt = asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream;
525prio_again:
526 /* Find the next stream to use */
527 if (strqt == NULL) {
528 strq = TAILQ_FIRST(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel);
529 } else {
530 strqn = TAILQ_NEXT(strqt, ss_params.prio.next_spoke);
531 if (strqn != NULL &&
532 strqn->ss_params.prio.priority == strqt->ss_params.prio.priority) {
533 strq = strqn;
534 } else {
535 strq = TAILQ_FIRST(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel);
536 }
537 }
538
539 /* If CMT is off, we must validate that
540 * the stream in question has the first
541 * item pointed towards are network destination
542 * requested by the caller. Note that if we
543 * turn out to be locked to a stream (assigning
544 * TSN's then we must stop, since we cannot
545 * look for another stream with data to send
546 * to that destination). In CMT's case, by
547 * skipping this check, we will send one
548 * data packet towards the requested net.
549 */
550 if (net != NULL && strq != NULL &&
551 SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_cmt_on_off) == 0) {
552 if (TAILQ_FIRST(&strq->outqueue) &&
553 TAILQ_FIRST(&strq->outqueue)->net != NULL &&
554 TAILQ_FIRST(&strq->outqueue)->net != net) {
555 if (strq == asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream) {
556 return (NULL);
557 } else {
558 strqt = strq;
559 goto prio_again;
560 }
561 }
562 }
563 return (strq);
564}
565
566static int
567sctp_ss_prio_get_value(struct sctp_tcb *stcb SCTP_UNUSED, struct sctp_association *asoc SCTP_UNUSED,
568 struct sctp_stream_out *strq, uint16_t *value)
569{
570 if (strq == NULL) {
571 return (-1);
572 }
573 *value = strq->ss_params.prio.priority;
574 return (1);
575}
576
577static int
578sctp_ss_prio_set_value(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_association *asoc,
579 struct sctp_stream_out *strq, uint16_t value)
580{
581 if (strq == NULL) {
582 return (-1);
583 }
584 strq->ss_params.prio.priority = value;
585 sctp_ss_prio_remove(stcb, asoc, strq, NULL, 1);
586 sctp_ss_prio_add(stcb, asoc, strq, NULL, 1);
587 return (1);
588}

590/*
591 * Fair bandwidth algorithm.
592 * Maintains an equal throughput per stream.
593 */
594static void
595sctp_ss_fb_clear(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_association *asoc,
596 int clear_values, int holds_lock)
597{
598 if (holds_lock == 0) {
599 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
600 }
601 while (!TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel)) {
602 struct sctp_stream_out *strq;
603
604 strq = TAILQ_FIRST(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel);
605 if (clear_values) {
606 strq->ss_params.fb.rounds = -1;
607 }
608 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel, strq, ss_params.fb.next_spoke);
609 strq->ss_params.fb.next_spoke.tqe_next = NULL;
610 strq->ss_params.fb.next_spoke.tqe_prev = NULL;
611 }
612 asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream = NULL;
613 if (holds_lock == 0) {
614 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
615 }
616 return;
617}
618
619static void
620sctp_ss_fb_init_stream(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_stream_out *strq, struct sctp_stream_out *with_strq)
621{
622 if (with_strq != NULL) {
623 if (stcb->asoc.ss_data.locked_on_sending == with_strq) {
624 stcb->asoc.ss_data.locked_on_sending = strq;
625 }
626 if (stcb->asoc.ss_data.last_out_stream == with_strq) {
627 stcb->asoc.ss_data.last_out_stream = strq;
628 }
629 }
630 strq->ss_params.fb.next_spoke.tqe_next = NULL;
631 strq->ss_params.fb.next_spoke.tqe_prev = NULL;
632 if (with_strq != NULL) {
633 strq->ss_params.fb.rounds = with_strq->ss_params.fb.rounds;
634 } else {
635 strq->ss_params.fb.rounds = -1;
636 }
637 return;
638}
639
640static void
641sctp_ss_fb_add(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_association *asoc,
642 struct sctp_stream_out *strq, struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp SCTP_UNUSED,
643 int holds_lock)
644{
645 if (holds_lock == 0) {
646 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
647 }
648 if (!TAILQ_EMPTY(&strq->outqueue) &&
649 (strq->ss_params.fb.next_spoke.tqe_next == NULL) &&
650 (strq->ss_params.fb.next_spoke.tqe_prev == NULL)) {
651 if (strq->ss_params.fb.rounds < 0)
652 strq->ss_params.fb.rounds = TAILQ_FIRST(&strq->outqueue)->length;
653 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel, strq, ss_params.fb.next_spoke);
654 }
655 if (holds_lock == 0) {
656 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
657 }
658 return;
659}
660
661static void
662sctp_ss_fb_remove(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_association *asoc,
663 struct sctp_stream_out *strq, struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp SCTP_UNUSED,
664 int holds_lock)
665{
666 if (holds_lock == 0) {
667 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
668 }
669 /* Remove from wheel if stream queue is empty and actually is on the wheel */
670 if (TAILQ_EMPTY(&strq->outqueue) &&
671 (strq->ss_params.fb.next_spoke.tqe_next != NULL ||
672 strq->ss_params.fb.next_spoke.tqe_prev != NULL)) {
673 if (asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream == strq) {
674 asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream = TAILQ_PREV(asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream, sctpwheel_listhead,
675 ss_params.fb.next_spoke);
676 if (asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream == NULL) {
677 asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream = TAILQ_LAST(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel,
678 sctpwheel_listhead);
679 }
680 if (asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream == strq) {
681 asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream = NULL;
682 }
683 }
684 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel, strq, ss_params.fb.next_spoke);
685 strq->ss_params.fb.next_spoke.tqe_next = NULL;
686 strq->ss_params.fb.next_spoke.tqe_prev = NULL;
687 }
688 if (holds_lock == 0) {
689 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
690 }
691 return;
692}
693
694static struct sctp_stream_out*
695sctp_ss_fb_select(struct sctp_tcb *stcb SCTP_UNUSED, struct sctp_nets *net,
696 struct sctp_association *asoc)
697{
698 struct sctp_stream_out *strq = NULL, *strqt;
699
700 if (asoc->ss_data.locked_on_sending) {
701 return (asoc->ss_data.locked_on_sending);
702 }
703 if (asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream == NULL ||
704 TAILQ_FIRST(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel) == TAILQ_LAST(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel, sctpwheel_listhead)) {
705 strqt = TAILQ_FIRST(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel);
706 } else {
707 strqt = TAILQ_NEXT(asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream, ss_params.fb.next_spoke);
708 }
709 do {
710 if ((strqt != NULL) &&
711 ((SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_cmt_on_off) > 0) ||
712 (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_cmt_on_off) == 0 &&
713 (net == NULL || (TAILQ_FIRST(&strqt->outqueue) && TAILQ_FIRST(&strqt->outqueue)->net == NULL) ||
714 (net != NULL && TAILQ_FIRST(&strqt->outqueue) && TAILQ_FIRST(&strqt->outqueue)->net != NULL &&
715 TAILQ_FIRST(&strqt->outqueue)->net == net))))) {
716 if ((strqt->ss_params.fb.rounds >= 0) && (strq == NULL ||
717 strqt->ss_params.fb.rounds < strq->ss_params.fb.rounds)) {
718 strq = strqt;
719 }
720 }
721 if (strqt != NULL) {
722 strqt = TAILQ_NEXT(strqt, ss_params.fb.next_spoke);
723 } else {
724 strqt = TAILQ_FIRST(&asoc->ss_data.out.wheel);
725 }
726 } while (strqt != strq);
727 return (strq);
728}
729
730static void
731sctp_ss_fb_scheduled(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_nets *net SCTP_UNUSED,
732 struct sctp_association *asoc, struct sctp_stream_out *strq,
733 int moved_how_much SCTP_UNUSED)
734{
735 struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp;
736 struct sctp_stream_out *strqt;
737 int subtract;
738
739 if (stcb->asoc.idata_supported == 0) {
740 sp = TAILQ_FIRST(&strq->outqueue);
741 if ((sp != NULL) && (sp->some_taken == 1)) {
742 stcb->asoc.ss_data.locked_on_sending = strq;
743 } else {
744 stcb->asoc.ss_data.locked_on_sending = NULL;
745 }
746 } else {
747 stcb->asoc.ss_data.locked_on_sending = NULL;
748 }
749 subtract = strq->ss_params.fb.rounds;
750 TAILQ_FOREACH(strqt, &asoc->ss_data.out.wheel, ss_params.fb.next_spoke) {
751 strqt->ss_params.fb.rounds -= subtract;
752 if (strqt->ss_params.fb.rounds < 0)
753 strqt->ss_params.fb.rounds = 0;
754 }
755 if (TAILQ_FIRST(&strq->outqueue)) {
756 strq->ss_params.fb.rounds = TAILQ_FIRST(&strq->outqueue)->length;
757 } else {
758 strq->ss_params.fb.rounds = -1;
759 }
760 asoc->ss_data.last_out_stream = strq;
761 return;
762}
763
764/*
765 * First-come, first-serve algorithm.
766 * Maintains the order provided by the application.
767 */
768static void
769sctp_ss_fcfs_add(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_association *asoc,
770 struct sctp_stream_out *strq SCTP_UNUSED,
771 struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp, int holds_lock);
772
773static void
774sctp_ss_fcfs_init(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_association *asoc,
775 int holds_lock)
776{
777 uint32_t x, n = 0, add_more = 1;
778 struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp;
779 uint16_t i;
780
781 if (holds_lock == 0) {
782 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
783 }
784 TAILQ_INIT(&asoc->ss_data.out.list);
785 /*
786 * If there is data in the stream queues already,
787 * the scheduler of an existing association has
788 * been changed. We can only cycle through the
789 * stream queues and add everything to the FCFS
790 * queue.
791 */
792 while (add_more) {
793 add_more = 0;
794 for (i = 0; i < stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt; i++) {
795 sp = TAILQ_FIRST(&stcb->asoc.strmout[i].outqueue);
796 x = 0;
797 /* Find n. message in current stream queue */
798 while (sp != NULL && x < n) {
799 sp = TAILQ_NEXT(sp, next);
800 x++;
801 }
802 if (sp != NULL) {
803 sctp_ss_fcfs_add(stcb, &stcb->asoc, &stcb->asoc.strmout[i], sp, 1);
804 add_more = 1;
805 }
806 }
807 n++;
808 }
809 if (holds_lock == 0) {
810 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
811 }
812 return;
813}
814
815static void
816sctp_ss_fcfs_clear(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_association *asoc,
817 int clear_values, int holds_lock)
818{
819 struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp;
820
821 if (clear_values) {
822 if (holds_lock == 0) {
823 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
824 }
825 while (!TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->ss_data.out.list)) {
826 sp = TAILQ_FIRST(&asoc->ss_data.out.list);
827 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->ss_data.out.list, sp, ss_next);
828 sp->ss_next.tqe_next = NULL;
829 sp->ss_next.tqe_prev = NULL;
830 }
831 if (holds_lock == 0) {
832 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
833 }
834 }
835 return;
836}
837
838static void
839sctp_ss_fcfs_init_stream(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_stream_out *strq, struct sctp_stream_out *with_strq)
840{
841 if (with_strq != NULL) {
842 if (stcb->asoc.ss_data.locked_on_sending == with_strq) {
843 stcb->asoc.ss_data.locked_on_sending = strq;
844 }
845 if (stcb->asoc.ss_data.last_out_stream == with_strq) {
846 stcb->asoc.ss_data.last_out_stream = strq;
847 }
848 }
849 strq->ss_params.fb.next_spoke.tqe_next = NULL;
850 strq->ss_params.fb.next_spoke.tqe_prev = NULL;
851 return;
852}
853
854static void
855sctp_ss_fcfs_add(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_association *asoc,
856 struct sctp_stream_out *strq SCTP_UNUSED, struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp,
857 int holds_lock)
858{
859 if (holds_lock == 0) {
860 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
861 }
862 if (sp && (sp->ss_next.tqe_next == NULL) &&
863 (sp->ss_next.tqe_prev == NULL)) {
864 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&asoc->ss_data.out.list, sp, ss_next);
865 }
866 if (holds_lock == 0) {
867 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
868 }
869 return;
870}
871
872static int
873sctp_ss_fcfs_is_empty(struct sctp_tcb *stcb SCTP_UNUSED, struct sctp_association *asoc)
874{
875 if (TAILQ_EMPTY(&asoc->ss_data.out.list)) {
876 return (1);
877 } else {
878 return (0);
879 }
880}
881
882static void
883sctp_ss_fcfs_remove(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_association *asoc,
884 struct sctp_stream_out *strq SCTP_UNUSED, struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp,
885 int holds_lock)
886{
887 if (holds_lock == 0) {
888 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
889 }
890 if (sp &&
891 ((sp->ss_next.tqe_next != NULL) ||
892 (sp->ss_next.tqe_prev != NULL))) {
893 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->ss_data.out.list, sp, ss_next);
894 sp->ss_next.tqe_next = NULL;
895 sp->ss_next.tqe_prev = NULL;
896 }
897 if (holds_lock == 0) {
898 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
899 }
900 return;
901}
902
903static struct sctp_stream_out *
904sctp_ss_fcfs_select(struct sctp_tcb *stcb SCTP_UNUSED, struct sctp_nets *net,
905 struct sctp_association *asoc)
906{
907 struct sctp_stream_out *strq;
908 struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp;
909
910 if (asoc->ss_data.locked_on_sending) {
911 return (asoc->ss_data.locked_on_sending);
912 }
913 sp = TAILQ_FIRST(&asoc->ss_data.out.list);
914default_again:
915 if (sp != NULL) {
916 strq = &asoc->strmout[sp->sid];
917 } else {
918 strq = NULL;
919 }
920
921 /*
922 * If CMT is off, we must validate that
923 * the stream in question has the first
924 * item pointed towards are network destination
925 * requested by the caller. Note that if we
926 * turn out to be locked to a stream (assigning
927 * TSN's then we must stop, since we cannot
928 * look for another stream with data to send
929 * to that destination). In CMT's case, by
930 * skipping this check, we will send one
931 * data packet towards the requested net.
932 */
933 if (net != NULL && strq != NULL &&
934 SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_cmt_on_off) == 0) {
935 if (TAILQ_FIRST(&strq->outqueue) &&
936 TAILQ_FIRST(&strq->outqueue)->net != NULL &&
937 TAILQ_FIRST(&strq->outqueue)->net != net) {
938 sp = TAILQ_NEXT(sp, ss_next);
939 goto default_again;
940 }
941 }
942 return (strq);
943}
